<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-446-122  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 446 122.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  May 14 1990 v7 n19 p19(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>LaserMaster PM driver to bring enhanced printing power to OS/2.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bernard, Diane.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   LaserMaster Corp. (product development).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentPrintersDevice DriversOS-2Fonts.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Diane BernardandM;Aiming to bolster OS/2 print capabilities, LaserMaster Corp. next month willdeliver a Presentation Manager (PM) driver for its printer controllers thatgives PM users high-performance output and font capabilities currentlylacking in OS/2 printer drivers, officials said.andM;LaserMaster's driver, which works with any of the firm's LX6 printercontrollers, speeds output by transmitting PM's graphical programminginterface (GPI) calls directly to the video interface of Hewlett-PackardCo.'s LaserJet printers, according to Bill Neuenschwander, third-partydevelopment manager at LaserMaster, based in Eden Prairie, Minn.andM;To fill gaps in existing OS/2 printer drivers, LaserMaster equipped thePresentation Manager driver with 135 outline fonts, according to companyofficials.andM;The controller also supports fonts from major vendors, including AdobeSystems Inc.'s PostScript fonts.andM;This added font support is a boon to Presentation Manager users, since OS/2'sexisting PostScript driver does not support downloaded PostScript fonts,according to Mike Sherwood, product manager at Aldus Corp., a softwaredeveloper based in Seattle.andM;LaserMaster will include the driver with its full range of printercontrollers -- including the $1,495 Series III Professional controller, whichsupports resolutions of 400 dots per inch (dpi), and the $2,995 Series IIIcontroller, which supports an 800-dpi resolution, according toNeuenschwander.andM;Current users of the LaserMaster controllers can purchase the driver for$100.andM;The driver requires 4M bytes of memory and LaserMaster release 3.0 software.andM;LaserMaster Corp. can be contacted at (612) 944-6069.andO;</TEXT></DOC>